#: paragraph:10,sentence:40
msgid "We agreed it would doubtless reach many more people before its zenith and that we simply couldn’t imagine its ongoing influence."
msgstr ""

#. Paragraph 10: Bill and I spoke about the Course’s longevity shortly before his passing. We agreed it would doubtless reach many more people before its zenith and that we simply couldn’t imagine its ongoing influenc...
#: paragraph:10,sentence:41
msgid "Both of us believed that those who had encountered the Course up to that point (in 1988) were the pathfinders, psychological pioneers who had volunteered to challenge the old precepts on which most of human experience has been based."
msgstr ""

#. Paragraph 10: Bill and I spoke about the Course’s longevity shortly before his passing. We agreed it would doubtless reach many more people before its zenith and that we simply couldn’t imagine its ongoing influenc...
#: paragraph:10,sentence:42
msgid "In every era, various seers and masters have comprehended the hypnotized state of the human condition and offered Truth as its remedy, but this modern group of pioneers represents a grassroots movement."
msgstr ""

#. Paragraph 10: Bill and I spoke about the Course’s longevity shortly before his passing. We agreed it would doubtless reach many more people before its zenith and that we simply couldn’t imagine its ongoing influenc...
#: paragraph:10,sentence:43
msgid "These are “ordinary people” questioning the status quo and claiming their right to be free of psychological bondage."
msgstr ""

